{"first_name":"Nikhil","last_name":"Kalghatgi","permalink":"nikhil-kalghatgi","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/nikhil-kalghatgi","homepage_url":null,"birthplace":null,"twitter_username":null,"blog_url":null,"blog_feed_url":null,"affiliation_name":"SoftBank Capital","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"angel, advisor, nyc","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Wed Sep 21 21:26:08 UTC 2011","updated_at":"Tue Sep 04 09:06:37 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Nikhil is an early-stage VC at SoftBank Capital and is based in NYC. He focuses on Seed and Series A consumer tech investments.  He is currently invested and/or actively involved in Mobile (e.g. Soundtracking, MocoSpace, Thumb, Piictu, JumpRamp), Social Marketing (e.g. BuddyMedia, Socialflow, Taykey, CrowdTwist), Consumer-Enterprise (e.g. BestVendor, PogoPlug), Funds (e.g. Lerer Ventures, TechStars, Gen Y Capital and more) and provides investment support for SoftBank Corporation (e.g. Zynga, Gilt Groupe)</p>\n\n<p>Nikhil was Founder and Fund-Manager of Partner 6 Investment Group, a hedge fund in Boston and then joined the founding team of Localytics, a mobile application analytics provider. Nikhil is a recovering engineer with several years of experience in front-end design and development focused on mobile and web UX before completing his MBA at Harvard Business School.\nFind him at @nikhilkal and omg.vc</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,103],"assets/images/resized/0018/4514/184514v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[210,145],"assets/images/resized/0018/4514/184514v2-max-250x250.jpg"],[[210,145],"assets/images/resized/0018/4514/184514v2-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":"<p><a href=\"http://www.softbank.com\" title=\"Softbank Capital\" rel=\"nofollow\">Softbank Capital</a></p>"},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"MBA","subject":"","institution":"Harvard Business School","graduated_year":null,"graduated_month":null,"graduated_day":null},{"degree_type":"MS","subject":"Engineering Management","institution"